-- Moscow Builder Mostotrest Raises $388 Million in Initial Public Offering
-- B y   B r a d   C o o k
-- 2010-11-03T05:34:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/mostotrest-raises-388-million-in-initial-public-offering.html
OAO Mostotrest raised $388 million in
an initial public offering, the Russian construction company
said in a statement today.  Mostotrest sold 62 million shares at $6.25 apiece, valuing
the company at $1.6 billion. Deutsche Bank AG, JPMorgan Chase &
Co. and Troika Dialog managed the sale.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Brad Cook at 
 bcook7@bloomberg.net  